69.4	Clifford_Stoll	Clifford Stoll	Clifford Stoll (or Cliff Stoll) is a U.S. astronomer and author. He is best known for his pursuit of hacker Markus Hess in 1986 and the subsequent 1989 book detailing his investigation. Stoll has authored a total of three books as well as technology articles in the non-specialist press (e.g., in Scientific American on the Curta mechanical calculator and the slide rule).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Acme_klein_bottle.jpg/120px-Acme_klein_bottle.jpg
